HEADWORD: Metasomatism
<hw>Met`a*so"ma*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + Gr. <?/, <?/, body.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>An
alteration in a mineral or rock mass when involving a chemical change of
the substance, as of chrysolite to serpentine; -- opposed to ordinary
<xex>metamorphism</xex>, as implying simply a recrystallization.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Met`a*so*mat"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metasome</ent>⟦br⟧
